

HELSINKI, Nov. 14 (Xinhua)-- The Finnish Ministry of Transport and Communications announced on Monday that it will start accepting applications for a license of commercial mobile TV license.

Finland has thus become the first European country to issue a license for a commercial TV service for mobile phones.

The service will be based on DVB-H (digital video broadcasting - handheld) transmission technology.

Finland is one of many countries experimenting with TV on mobile phones. TV service for mobile phones has been tested last spring in a trial network in its capital, Helsinki. Around 500 people were involved in the test, which showed mobile TV was favorably received.

Susanna Huovinen, the transport and Communications minister, said that the government wants to promote the development of innovations, including mobile TV.

The operating license will be awarded early next year.

